1. Benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH)
2. Dysuria (difficulty urinating)
3. Urinary incontinence (inability to control urinary stream)
4. Male hypogonadism (low testosterone)
5. Diabetes mellitus (diabetes)
6. Paresthesia (numbness or tingling)
7. Bowel incontinence (inability to control bowel movements)
8. Unsteady gait (uncoordinated gait)
9. Hyporeflexia of lower limbs (low reflexes in the legs)
10. Abnormal intervertebral disk morphology (abnormal shape of the intervertebral disks)
